sub_title: Architect & Urban Practitioner and Researcher | International Trade & Development Consultant
summary: Architect, an urban practitioner, currently studying a Research Master in Urban Economic Geography. Experienced in the public sector coordinating multiple actors for public space interventions and master plans for cities and rural communities in Ecuador. Always trying to raise the voices of the users and all actors in dialogue into the discussion. A firm believer of the collaborative construction of processes to achieve optimal results and seeing the beauty in simple daily things that inspire our lives. Currently, she is conducting research on the impact of vegetation in cities.
